 491:../../CM7/LWIP/Target/ethernetif.c **** /**
 492:../../CM7/LWIP/Target/ethernetif.c ****  * @brief This function should be called when a packet is ready to be read
 493:../../CM7/LWIP/Target/ethernetif.c ****  * from the interface. It uses the function low_level_input() that
 494:../../CM7/LWIP/Target/ethernetif.c ****  * should handle the actual reception of bytes from the network
 495:../../CM7/LWIP/Target/ethernetif.c ****  * interface. Then the type of the received packet is determined and
 496:../../CM7/LWIP/Target/ethernetif.c ****  * the appropriate input function is called.
 497:../../CM7/LWIP/Target/ethernetif.c ****  *
